---
// Required on every monetized page. The Policy Engine's disclosure check
// blocks any PR that adds affiliate links to a page without this component
// (plan §5.3), so removing it from a template is not a thing an agent can do.
//
// This is a protected path in policy/rules.yml — edits need human approval.
// Wording is a legal/trust commitment (spec §13), not copy to optimize.
---

<aside class="affiliate-disclosure" role="note" aria-label="Affiliate disclosure">
  <p>
    <strong>Disclosure:</strong> This page contains affiliate links. If you buy
    through one of them we may earn a commission, at no extra cost to you. This
    never affects which products we recommend or how we rank them — our
    recommendations are based on the research and testing described on this
    page. Content on this site is produced with AI assistance and reviewed
    before publication.
  </p>
</aside>

<style>
  .affiliate-disclosure {
    border-left: 3px solid currentColor;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .affiliate-disclosure p {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
